      "body" : "@TacB0sS you can use <code>enum</code> in annotatios, but they are not compile-time constant. The difference becomes apparent when you write <code>static final EnumType VARIABLE = EnumType.ENUM_CONSTANT;</code> and try to use <code>VARIABLE</code> in an annotation; it won’t work. You can only use <code>EnumType.ENUM_CONSTANT</code> which is not a constant expression, but specifically allowed in annotations (and <code>switch</code> statements)."
