    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>I am thinking this may not be possible in Java because annotation and its parameters are resolved at compile time. </p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>With Seam 2 <a href=\"http://seamframework.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://seamframework.org/</a> you were able to resolve annotation parameters at runtime, with expression language inside double quotes. </p>\n\n<p>In Seam 3 <a href=\"http://seamframework.org/Seam3/Solder\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://seamframework.org/Seam3/Solder</a>, this feature is the module Seam Solder </p>\n"
